    <header>
      <div class="logo">RV</div>
      <div>
        <h1>RV Roadwise — A friendly guide to picking & caring for a nice RV</h1>
        <p class="lead">Everything you need: buying checklist, packing lists, maintenance, trip planning, and a gallery to inspire you.</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="grid">
      <main>
        <section class="section card">
          <h2>Quick Overview</h2>
          <p>RVs come in many shapes. The most common classes are:</p>
          <div class="feature-list" style="margin-top:10px">
            <div class="feature"><strong>Class A</strong> — Bus-like luxury motorhomes, spacious, higher cost.</div>
            <div class="feature"><strong>Class B</strong> — Camper vans, compact, easy to drive and park.</div>
            <div class="feature"><strong>Class C</strong> — Mid-size with over-cab sleeping area — balanced choice.</div>
            <div class="feature"><strong>Travel Trailer</strong> — Towable, wide range of sizes and price points.</div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section card" id="buying-checklist">
          <h2>Buying Checklist</h2>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li><strong>Budget:</strong> Purchase price + insurance + maintenance + campground fees.</li>
            <li><strong>Floorplan:</strong> Consider sleeping arrangement, bathroom placement, kitchen size.</li>
            <li><strong>Drivability:</strong> Tow vehicle capacity or driver's comfort with a larger motorhome.</li>
            <li><strong>Age & Condition:</strong> Get vehicle history, inspect roof, plumbing, appliances.</li>
            <li><strong>Test Drive & Systems Check:</strong> AC, heater, fridge on LP/electric, water pumps, slide-outs.</li>
            <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Title, VIN check, service records, warranty transfer.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section card" id="must-haves">
          <h2>Must-have Equipment</h2>
          <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap">
            <div style="flex:1;min-width:220px">
              <h3 style="margin:0 0 8px 0">Safety & Driving</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Roadside emergency kit (flares, jumper cables, basic tools)</li>
                <li>Tire pressure gauge & spare tire / jack rated for the RV</li>
                <li>Backup camera or spotter for larger rigs</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div style="flex:1;min-width:220px">
              <h3 style="margin:0 0 8px 0">Camp Setup</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Leveling blocks, wheel chocks, 30/50 amp adapters (as needed)</li>
                <li>Freshwater hose (drinking-safe) and sewer hose kit</li>
                <li>Surge protector and extension cord rated for RV use</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section card" id="maintenance">
          <h2>Basic Maintenance & Seasonal Care</h2>
          <p>Keep an RV in top shape by following a simple routine:</p>
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Task</th><th>Frequency</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Check tire pressure & tread</td><td>Before long trips / monthly</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Inspect roof seams & seals</td><td>Twice a year</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Service generator & engine</td><td>Per manufacturer schedule</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Flush water heater & winterize plumbing</td><td>Yearly / before winter storage</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </section>

        <section class="section card" id="packing">
          <h2>Packing & Organization</h2>
          <p>Smart packing saves space and reduces frustration. Use clear bins, over-door organizers, and a small toolbox dedicated to the RV.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Kitchen: stackable pans, folding dish rack, spice kit</li>
            <li>Bedroom: compact linens, travel pillows, blackout shades</li>
            <li>Outdoor: folding table, camp chairs, tarp, portable grill</li>
            <li>Electronics: power bank, USB hub, cable organizers</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section card" id="trip-planning">
          <h2>Trip Planning Tips</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Plan driving distances conservatively — allow more time for stops and scenic routes.</li>
            <li>Reserve campgrounds in peak seasons; look for RV-friendly amenities (dump station, hookups).</li>
            <li>Use apps and forums to verify clearance heights, road restrictions, and gate widths.</li>
            <li>Have a basic backup plan for boondocking or alternate sites if your first choice is full.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="section card" id="recommended-models">
          <h2>Popular Picks (general suggestions)</h2>
          <p>Here are widely-recommended models across categories — research current model years & reviews before buying.</p>
          <table>
            <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Example Models</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Class A</td><td>Winnebago Horizon, Tiffin Allegro</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Class B</td><td>Winnebago Travato, Mercedes Sprinter conversions</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Class C</td><td>Jayco Redhawk, Thor Four Winds</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Travel Trailer</td><td>Airstream, Keystone Cougar</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </section>

